#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:1
msgid "Role and Expectations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:3
msgid ""
"The role of the Regional Coordinators is to be the front face of the "
"Carpentries, promoting our work and our culture in their geographical "
"area.  The Regional Coordniators will manage workshop logistics, "
"communicate with hosts and instructors, and respond to general inquiries."
"  As a team, all administrators will work together to support each other "
"and ensure communities can thrive locally while maintaining quality and "
"consistency globally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:5
msgid "This includes the following responsibilities"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:7
msgid ""
"Attend monthly admin team meetings.  Time zones will be taken into "
"consideration when scheduling these meetings.  Attending other "
"Carpentries community meetings is also highly recommended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:8
msgid ""
"Read emails sent to the admin group. Stay up to date on all Carpentries "
"operations as outlined in the Carpentries handbook. Respond to workshop "
"requests from host sites in your region within two business days. This "
"may include, but is not limited to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:11
msgid "Sharing general Carpentries information"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:12
msgid "Recruiting instructors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:13
msgid "Setting up surveys and registration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:14
msgid "Supporting other planning logistics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:15
msgid "Recording all information according to Carpentries’ systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:16
msgid ""
"Follow up on all completed workshops to collect attendance data and other"
" feedback, and record this in Carpentries’ systems."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:17
msgid ""
"Serve as the “front face” of the Carpentries in their region by "
"responding to general public inquiries and supporting our larger "
"communication efforts and other initiatives."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:18
msgid ""
"Communicate Carpentries community values to instructors, host sites, and "
"others constituents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:19
msgid ""
"Communicate successes and challenges with Carpentries Workshop and "
"Logistics Manager and other Regional Coordinators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:20
msgid ""
"Promote the Carpentries culture of an inclusive and supportive learning "
"environment informed by best practices in pedagogical research. Follow "
"the Carpentries Code of Conduct and report any violations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/workshop_administration/expectations.md:21
msgid "Elevate questions and issues to Carpentries staff as needed."
msgstr ""

